# Triaged container image CVEs for the Trivy scan in CI (OB-086).
#
# Add one advisory id per line (CVE-XXXX-NNNN or GHSA-xxxx) to suppress a
# HIGH/CRITICAL finding that has been reviewed and accepted, with a comment
# explaining why. Fixable vulnerabilities should be fixed (rebuild on a newer
# base image / bump the dependency) rather than ignored.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# npm-bundled toolchain (node:26 base image) — not application code
# These packages ship inside /usr/local/lib/node_modules/npm/node_modules/
# and are owned by the Node.js / npm release cadence, not this project.
# They will be resolved when the base image is updated via Dependabot.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# adm-zip 0.5.17 — bundled inside npm's copy of node-gyp; fix: 0.6.0
CVE-2026-39244

# sigstore 3.1.0 — bundled inside npm for publish provenance; fix: 4.1.1
CVE-2026-48815

# picomatch 4.0.3 — bundled inside npm's own glob tooling; fix: 4.0.4
# (The dev-dep instance at 4.0.1 is pruned from the runtime image.)
CVE-2026-33671

# undici 6.26.0 — bundled inside npm's own HTTP client; fix: 6.27.0
# usr/local/lib/node_modules/npm/node_modules/undici — not application code.
CVE-2026-12151

# brace-expansion 5.0.6 — bundled inside npm's glob tooling; fix: 5.0.7
# usr/local/lib/node_modules/npm/node_modules/brace-expansion — not application code.
CVE-2026-13149

# tar 7.5.16 — bundled inside npm for pack/publish; fix: 7.5.18 / 7.5.19
# usr/local/lib/node_modules/npm/node_modules/tar — not application code.
CVE-2026-59873
CVE-2026-59874

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# next.js — web-app framework present in workspace node_modules but NEVER
# imported or executed by the API container.  The CVEs involve request
# routing / middleware in the Next.js server; none are reachable because
# next.js is never started.  The proper long-term fix is to separate the
# web workspace from the API image build (tracked as a follow-up).
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
CVE-2026-44573
CVE-2026-44578
GHSA-8h8q-6873-q5fj
GHSA-h25m-26qc-wcjf
GHSA-q4gf-8mx6-v5v3
